    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-03-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-08-19T18:01:14Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow affiliated life and non-life insurance companies to file consolidated tax returns. </p> <p>Allows: (1) a phasein, between 2007 and 2013, of the full application of losses of affiliated non-life insurance companies against the taxable income of an affiliated life insurance company; and (2) an automatic waiver of the five-year waiting period applicable to affiliated non-life insurance companies for offset of their losses against life insurance company income. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to permit the consolidation of life insurance companies with other companies.</title>
